# JavaScript Class Structure Introduction

```javascript
// Class declaration
class Animal {
    constructor(name, species) {
        this.name = name;
        this.species = species;
    }

    describe() {
        return `${this.name} is a/an ${this.species}`;
    }
}

// Creating an instance of the Animal class
const dog = new Animal('Buddy', 'dog');
console.log(dog.describe()); // Output: Buddy is a/an dog
```

### Key Concepts:

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Class | Blueprint for creating objects |
| Instance | Specific object created from a class |
| Constructor | Method for initializing class properties |
| Method | Function associated with an object |

# Extending Classes and Inheritance

```javascript
// Base class
class Animal {
    constructor(name, species) {
        this.name = name;
        this.species = species;
    }

    describe() {
        return `${this.name} is a/an ${this.species}`;
    }
}

// Subclass extending Animal
class Dog extends Animal {
    constructor(name, breed) {
        super(name, 'dog');
        this.breed = breed;
    }

    bark() {
        return `${this.name} barks!`;
    }
}

// Creating a dog object
const pet = new Dog('Snowy', 'Labrador');
console.log(pet.describe()); // Output: Snowy is a/an dog
console.log(pet.bark()); // Output: Snowy barks!
```

